  "texts": [
    "We use 100-NN queries to evaluate dataset complexity because a higher k improves the estimation of LID and LRC (Eqs.",
    "5-6), and to assess the different SS strategies because the higher the k the more overhead for seed selection.Measures.",
    "We measure the wall clock time and distance calculations for both indexing and query answering.",
    "We also measure the accuracy of each k-NN query using Recall which quantifies the fraction of the true nearest neighbors that the query 𝑆 𝑄 successfully returns.Procedure.",
    "We tune each method to achieve the best trade-offs in accuracy/efficiency."
